<span id="Description"></span>
==Beschreibung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:Draft_AddToLayer.svg|24px]] '''Draft AddToLayer''' command adds objects to a layer, or removes them from any layer. {{Version|1.1}}
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Anwendung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select one or more objects.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Draft_AddToLayer.svg|16px]] [[Draft_AddToLayer|Add to layer...]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Utilities → [[Image:Draft_AddToLayer.svg|16px]] Add to layer...}} option from the menu, or from the [[Tree_view|Tree view]] or [[3D_view|3D view]] context menu.
# A menu is displayed near the cursor. Do one of the following:
#* Select {{MenuCommand|[[Image:List-remove.svg|16px]] Remove from layer}} to remove the objects from the layer they are in.
#* Select the layer you want to add the objects to.
#* Select {{MenuCommand|[[Image:List-add.svg|16px]] Add to new layer...}} to add the objects to a new layer:
#*# The {{MenuCommand|Create new layer}} dialog box opens.
#*# Enter a {{MenuCommand|Layer name}}.
#*# Press the {{Button|OK}} button.
</div>


